By multiplying these complex numbers, we have:
$$Q \cdot E \cdot D = (21-5i) \cdot (11+5i) \cdot (2i)$$
To multiply complex numbers, we multiply each real part and imaginary part separately and then combine the complex parts. 
\begin{align*}
(21-5i) \cdot (11+5i)
&= 21 \cdot 11 + 21 \cdot 5i - 5i \cdot 11 - 5i \cdot 5i\\
&= 231 + 11 \cdot 5i + 5i \cdot 5i\\
&= 231 + 55i + 25i^2\\
&= 231 + 55i - 25i^2\\
&= 231 + 55i - 25(-1)\\
&= 231 + 55i + 25\\
&= 256 + 55i
\end{align*} Now we have $(256+55i)(2i)$. We multiply this expression as follows:
\begin{align*}
(256+55i)(2i)
&= 256 \cdot 2i + 55i \cdot 2i\\
&= 512i + 110i\\
&= 622i
\end{align*}
Therefore, $Q \cdot E \cdot D$ is $\boxed{622i}$.
